Commit Message: arXiv LaTeX cleaner moved to its own repo from https://github.com/google-research/google-research/tree/master/arxiv_latex_cleaner.
Add option to compress PDF images using Ghostscript
Minor styling edits. Fixing broken test.
Adding the option to remove commands and environments (for now \begin{comment}\end{comment})
Copying only the referenced TeX files outside the root
Better tex inclusion detection. README updated.
Better tex inclusion detection. README updated.

Allow commands_to_delete to work with nested commands

This commit introduces the possibility to execute commands_to_delete
with nested commands (issue #9) by improving the regex expression
that matches the user-defined custom command.
It also improves the regex expression used to match comments environment
that was affected by the same problem.

Limitation #1: in commands_to_delete max 2 nested levels are supported.
Limitation #2: the \end{comment} has to be followed by a newline character.
Updated tests with nested commands support
Fixing tests after PR. Leaving the comment sign at the end of the line is necessary not to affect spacings.

Update requirements.txt

I was installing arxiv-latex-cleaner in a vanilla notebook and received this error: "ImportError: No module named setuptools"

Updating the requirements to install setuptools fixed this.
